# Apex -> www redirector (koyracloud utility service).
#
# Purpose: some DNS providers (e.g. Google Cloud DNS, Squarespace-managed) can
# neither CNAME nor ALIAS a zone apex, and koyracloud's Cloudflare-for-SaaS only
# activates a custom hostname via a CNAME — so a bare apex can't be served or
# redirected through the normal hidden tunnel path. This tiny service fills that
# gap: it 301-redirects <apex> -> https://www.<apex><path>, with a real
# Let's Encrypt cert (HTTP-01 works here because WAN2:80 is port-forwarded to
# this service — the inbound path the Cloudflare tunnel can't provide).
#
# Exposure: reached ONLY via a public port-forward (:80 -> <node>:8081, :443 ->
# <node>:8443). www and all real app traffic still flow through the hidden CF
# tunnel; only the bare apex touches this WAN path. If it's down, only apex
# redirects break — the sites keep working on www.
#
# To onboard an apex: add a block below (host -> https://www.host) and redeploy
# (bump the config version in deploy/apex-redirect-stack.yml). ACME_EMAIL is
# supplied as an env var by the stack file.

{
	http_port 8081
	https_port 8443
	email {$ACME_EMAIL}
}

# Replace with the apex domains you want to redirect to their www host:
example.com {
	redir https://www.example.com{uri} permanent
}
